{"ALL":[{"def":"The whole quantity, extent, duration, amount, quality, or degree of; the whole; the whole number of; any whatever; every; as, all the wheat; all the land; all the year; all the strength; all happiness; all abundance; loss of all power; beyond all doubt; you will see us all (or all of us).","pos":""}],"ALL FOOLS' DAY":[{"def":"The first day of April, a day on which sportive impositions are practiced.","pos":""}],"ALL FOURS":[{"def":"All four legs of a quadruped; or the two legs and two arms of a person.","pos":""}],"ALL HAIL":[{"def":"All health; -- a phrase of salutation or welcome.","pos":""}],"ALL SOULS' DAY":[{"def":"The second day of November; a feast day of the Roman Catholic church, on which supplications are made for the souls of the faithful dead.","pos":""}],"ALL-HAIL":[{"def":"To salute; to greet.","pos":""}],"ALL-POSSESSED":[{"def":"Controlled by an evil spirit or by evil passions; wild.","pos":""},{"def":"The first day of November, called, also, Allhallows or Hallowmas; a feast day kept in honor of all the saints; also, the season of this festival.","pos":""}]}